WEBVTT

00:00.994 --> 00:08.263
One of my daughters is turning 16 in a couple of weeks, and so she's currently studying for her written test for a driver's license.

00:08.283 --> 00:12.629
Now in a teenager's mind, this is one of the most important tests, isn't it?

00:13.009 --> 00:16.233
Because if you pass, it opens up new possibilities.

00:17.475 --> 00:22.962
Recently, I came across a stack of boxes of COVID tests in a closet.

00:23.426 --> 00:25.168
I'm so sorry to remind you of that memory.

00:25.629 --> 00:31.996
What an uncomfortable test that was sticking that oversized Q-tip up your nose until you cried.

00:32.056 --> 00:33.177
It was horrible.

00:34.098 --> 00:38.984
My husband's company required him to take the test every Monday for over a year.

00:39.825 --> 00:45.932
A test failure meant isolation, disappointment, and for many caused fear.

00:46.693 --> 00:49.476
Fear that life as they knew it was about to change.

00:50.637 --> 00:51.378
The purpose

00:51.554 --> 00:58.283
of any test is to measure the quality, the skill, the knowledge, or the resolve of someone.

00:59.284 --> 01:11.441
In life, we face many tests, some for education or a job, others for our health or a well-being, and we test each other, evaluating the quality of our relationships.

01:12.262 --> 01:14.645
Tests are designed to see if we measure up.

01:15.987 --> 01:18.290
And none of these tests that I've mentioned,

01:18.658 --> 01:25.786
None would compare to what I would declare the most rigorous test ever given in all of history.

01:27.068 --> 01:28.770
Turn over to the first book of the Bible.

01:29.671 --> 01:31.794
We're going to begin in Genesis chapter 22.

01:33.856 --> 01:42.226
Genesis chapter 22 verse 1 says, some time later, God tested Abraham.

01:43.618 --> 01:47.383
Now that line just brings to mind so many questions.

01:47.883 --> 01:54.111
Did God only test the patriarch Abraham because he was the one who he was going to make a covenant with?

01:54.932 --> 01:57.074
Did God test other people in the Bible?

01:58.096 --> 02:00.078
Why would God test his people?

02:00.579 --> 02:04.463
And if he did test people in the Bible, does he still test people today?

02:04.504 --> 02:08.629
And would he ever test us in the same way that he tested Abraham?

02:09.910 --> 02:11.492
Okay, one thing at a time.

02:11.812 --> 02:13.074
Let's begin with looking at

02:13.314 --> 02:15.477
who God tested, Abraham.

02:16.418 --> 02:18.701
He is the one that God made the covenant with.

02:20.003 --> 02:29.156
It's mentioned in Genesis 12, verses one through three, it says, the Lord had said to Abram, leave your country, your people and your father's household and go to the land I will show you.

02:29.857 --> 02:32.740
I will make you into a great nation and I will bless you.

02:33.502 --> 02:35.805
I will make your name great and you will be a blessing.

02:36.145 --> 02:39.750
I will bless those who bless you and whoever curses you, I will curse.

02:40.471 --> 02:42.674
And all peoples on earth will be blessed.

02:42.914 --> 02:43.355
through you.

02:45.017 --> 02:52.108
Now these verses do not actually begin with the words God tested Abram, but it certainly sounds like a test to me.

02:53.189 --> 02:56.794
Is the thought of God testing offensive to you?

02:58.116 --> 02:59.158
Now here's the thing to remember.

02:59.599 --> 03:00.640
Not all tests are bad.

03:02.002 --> 03:04.065
I know some of you would disagree with me on that.

03:04.486 --> 03:09.313
Many parents, teachers, and even coaches, they worry about the perils of competition.

03:10.014 --> 03:12.818
And they would rather encourage self-esteem and self-worth

03:13.154 --> 03:17.761
because everybody's got to be a winner, so prizes and ribbons for all the participants.

03:18.522 --> 03:19.924
Well, true love, we imagine.

03:20.304 --> 03:28.316
It does not challenge or judge, but that means you avoid acknowledging that every one of us falls short.

03:29.177 --> 03:35.246
See, a test could be viewed as an opportunity, an opportunity to prove that you're just ready to do a task.

03:35.266 --> 03:40.594
For example, here, Abram is asked to leave the land and the people that he knew, and to go follow God.

03:41.442 --> 03:43.604
God was testing Abram's loyalty.

03:44.565 --> 03:49.191
We can read on and find that Abram passed this test as he packed up and he followed God.

03:50.032 --> 03:58.641
But when he feared people, the people around him, more than what he trusted God, he failed the test.

03:59.342 --> 04:01.084
And then he lied about who his wife was.

04:02.926 --> 04:04.408
But God did not give up on Abram.

04:05.108 --> 04:10.194
He had a significant role in God's plan and God tested Abram more than once.

04:11.714 --> 04:14.377
Second question, did God test others?

04:15.558 --> 04:23.505
In Genesis chapter two, we read about how our Creator God, he made the heavens and the earth, and then he formed man out of the dust of the earth.

04:24.266 --> 04:30.872
In chapter two, verses 15 to 17, it says, the Lord God placed the man in the garden of Eden to tend and watch over it.

04:31.433 --> 04:41.202
But the Lord God warned him, you may freely eat the fruit of every tree in the garden, except just that one tree, the tree of knowledge of good and evil.

04:42.754 --> 04:44.336
Well, that sounds like a test to me too.

04:45.258 --> 04:48.242
See, the very first human being ever created was tested.

04:49.443 --> 04:50.465
And he failed the test.

04:51.246 --> 04:55.592
A deceptive creature tempted them to eat from the tree of knowing good and bad.

04:56.053 --> 04:58.917
But the choice was still theirs to make.

05:00.139 --> 05:04.244
The authors of the BibleProject.com described it like this.

05:04.745 --> 05:10.994
The difference between the test from God and the temptation from the enemy is that the one who is testing

05:11.266 --> 05:12.888
has your best interest in mind.

05:13.569 --> 05:21.577
See, God puts a test before humans to see if they would respond with faithfulness or are they going to act in their own wisdom in disobedience.

05:22.598 --> 05:26.463
This wasn't some arbitrary test conducted by a cruel God.

05:27.284 --> 05:35.833
The scene in the Garden of Eden and the choice between our own path or abundant life in God is something that all people must face.

05:36.974 --> 05:40.338
God designed humans to be co-creators.

05:40.802 --> 05:42.384
co-rulers with Him.

05:43.065 --> 05:46.009
That's what it means to be bearing the image of God.

05:46.811 --> 05:53.320
And so by right then, God should test His image-bearers to determine what to entrust to them.

05:55.262 --> 05:58.908
Moses, He shows up a few generations after Abraham.

05:59.549 --> 06:02.032
He led God's people from Egypt to the promised land.

06:02.673 --> 06:05.397
They wandered in the wilderness for 40 years.

06:06.098 --> 06:09.042
And Deuteronomy 8.2 says that God humbled them

06:09.250 --> 06:11.592
by testing them to prove their character.

06:12.533 --> 06:17.618
In Exodus 15, it says, the Lord set before them a standard to test their faithfulness to him.

06:18.019 --> 06:24.465
He wanted to measure whether or not they listened carefully to him and if they did what was right and if they obeyed.

06:25.065 --> 06:33.253
And one of the tests that was provided was he would provide manna for them to eat and he told them, collect it every day, but not on Sundays.

06:33.834 --> 06:37.938
And those who disobeyed, they found it to be moldy and crawling with maggots.

06:38.914 --> 06:41.076
Now we're only the second book into the Bible.

06:41.137 --> 06:42.578
We can easily answer the question.

06:43.439 --> 06:46.042
Does God repeatedly test his people?

06:47.344 --> 06:47.584
Yes.

06:49.246 --> 06:51.128
Okay, let's focus again on Abraham.

06:52.229 --> 06:54.612
Lots of life experiences happen.

06:54.752 --> 06:57.495
They're all recorded about Abraham's life.

06:57.595 --> 07:07.026
And specifically in chapter 15, we read about how Abraham reminded God that he remained childless to which God made a promise to him.

07:07.266 --> 07:13.453
Genesis 15 verse 5, it says, He took Him outside and said, Look up at the heavens.

07:14.033 --> 07:14.894
Count the stars.

07:15.475 --> 07:21.221
And if indeed you can count them, then He said to them, Said to Him, So shall your offspring be.

07:22.442 --> 07:28.028
Abram and Sarai, they assumed God needed some help with fulfilling His promise.

07:28.048 --> 07:33.394
So Sarai suggests to Abram that her maidservant be something of a surrogate.

07:33.666 --> 07:37.149
And so he sleeps with her and then Hagar has indeed a son.

07:38.310 --> 07:45.758
But that plan, it causes jealousy, there's abuse, and a lot of drama, surprise, surprise.

07:46.779 --> 07:50.883
Abram had failed the test of trusting God's wisdom over his own.

07:52.004 --> 07:56.528
So God let some time pass, but he did not give up on him.

07:57.089 --> 07:58.330
Actually, the opposite happened.

07:58.650 --> 08:01.493
He gave him a new name to confirm the covenant.

08:02.133 --> 08:02.674
Abram

08:02.850 --> 08:08.036
became Abraham, which means the father of a multitude.

08:08.056 --> 08:10.799
13 years later, the Lord visits Abram.

08:11.220 --> 08:17.667
And he's told that the following year, when Abram would then be a hundred years old, that he was going to return.

08:18.348 --> 08:24.675
And so Genesis 18, verses 10 to 12 say, then the Lord said, I will surely return to you about this time next year.

08:24.815 --> 08:27.218
And Sarah, your wife will have a son.

08:27.906 --> 08:34.213
Sarah was listening to this conversation from the tent, Abraham and Sarah were both very old at this time.

08:34.333 --> 08:36.996
And Sarah was long past the age of having children.

08:37.516 --> 08:44.444
So she laughed silently to herself and said, how could a worn out woman like me enjoy such pleasure?

08:44.964 --> 08:48.488
Especially when my master, my husband is also so old.

08:50.931 --> 08:57.458
In December, 2022, when I found out that I was pregnant at the age of 45,

08:58.146 --> 09:00.468
I went and had my first appointment with the doctor.

09:00.889 --> 09:10.339
And after he explained that I would have to have an ultrasound every two weeks because I was advanced in maternity age.

09:11.380 --> 09:12.301
He couldn't help himself.

09:12.742 --> 09:13.863
He started to laugh.

09:13.883 --> 09:15.845
He slapped his knee even.

09:15.985 --> 09:18.248
And he said, oh, people are going to laugh about this.

09:19.769 --> 09:24.634
Now, I know that 45 is, of course, not 90.

09:24.755 --> 09:28.018
So maybe I shouldn't be comparing my story to Sarah.

09:28.802 --> 09:30.224
I experienced the laughs.

09:31.985 --> 09:39.073
Genesis 21, verses one through three, it says, the Lord kept his word did for Sarah exactly what he promised.

09:39.413 --> 09:40.214
She became pregnant.

09:40.895 --> 09:47.362
She gave birth to a son for Abraham in his old age, and this happened at just the time God said it would.

09:48.103 --> 09:55.631
And Abraham named their son Isaac, verses six through seven says, and Sarah declared, God has brought me laughter.

09:56.692 --> 09:58.354
All who hear about this,

09:58.626 --> 10:00.389
will laugh with me.

10:01.591 --> 10:07.840
Who would have said to Abraham that Sarah would nurse a baby yet I have given Abraham a son in his old age?

10:10.084 --> 10:16.574
When Sarah laughed, the Lord responded with, is anything too hard for the Lord?

10:18.016 --> 10:19.999
And he proved it isn't.

10:21.582 --> 10:23.865
God was faithful to keep his promise to Abraham.

10:24.366 --> 10:25.087
He gave him a son.

10:25.748 --> 10:26.770
Isaac was growing up.

10:27.234 --> 10:31.199
And with all of that backstory in mind, we come to our text.

10:32.200 --> 10:34.502
If you've been flipping around, go back to Genesis 22.

10:35.624 --> 10:41.130
Verse 1, again, it says, some time later, God tested Abraham.

10:43.192 --> 10:51.442
Notice, God tested, not Satan, not Abraham himself, but God, Elohim, the creator of life.

10:52.834 --> 10:56.780
This verse clearly makes the point that what follows is divine testing.

10:56.840 --> 10:58.302
It's not a demonic temptation.

10:59.684 --> 11:05.613
Genesis 22, verse one continues, it says, Abraham, God called, yes, he replied, here I am.

11:06.494 --> 11:10.841
See, Abraham's relationship with the Lord has strengthened over his hundred plus years.

11:11.161 --> 11:14.506
He knows God's power and God's ability to do the impossible.

11:14.587 --> 11:16.349
So he responds when he's called upon.

11:17.531 --> 11:20.195
Verse two, take your son, your only son.

11:20.996 --> 11:22.258
Yes, Isaac.

11:22.626 --> 11:24.248
whom you love so much.

11:25.851 --> 11:30.657
Abraham's first son, Ishmael, he was not an offspring of the promise.

11:31.579 --> 11:36.886
And the clarification that God gives, he's gradually intensifying terms he uses.

11:37.968 --> 11:43.255
It makes it undeniably clear to Abraham that it's Isaac, God is speaking about.

11:44.036 --> 11:48.242
The son, Abraham and Sarah had waited years for.

11:49.314 --> 11:51.437
Take Isaac, go to the land of Mariah.

11:51.637 --> 11:55.522
Now the land of Mariah, it's a significant place and we're gonna talk about that in just a few minutes.

11:57.445 --> 12:02.893
Verse two continues, go and sacrifice him as a burnt offering on one of the mountains that I will show you.

12:03.954 --> 12:08.781
Now technically any offering burned over an altar was a burnt offering.

12:09.061 --> 12:15.770
But in more specific terms, the burnt offering was the complete destruction of the animal, up in smoke.

12:16.551 --> 12:18.674
It was a sacrifice of general atonement.

12:19.266 --> 12:25.175
It's an acknowledgement of the sin nature and a request for renewed relationship with God.

12:26.477 --> 12:32.005
Now notice here, Abraham did not verbally object to God's command.

12:33.528 --> 12:42.502
This is evidence that child sacrifice as a mode of worship was acceptable in that time among the neighboring peoples and the cults.

12:43.042 --> 12:48.050
And I suspect that Abraham would not have known that his God

12:48.162 --> 12:49.624
was against human sacrifice.

12:50.164 --> 13:02.319
Now, later on, when Moses wrote the law, it became very clear, Leviticus 18 and chapter 20, that lists the command very specifically, you should not give your child by fire to Moloch.

13:02.339 --> 13:06.224
But the people, they did not always obey.

13:06.244 --> 13:12.571
And Josiah, in 2 Kings 23, he had to purge this practice from his people.

13:13.873 --> 13:18.098
It's easy for me to sit back and say, that's disgusting.

13:18.818 --> 13:23.285
But back then, they seemed to need the prophet Micah to clarify.

13:24.027 --> 13:24.427
And he did.

13:24.628 --> 13:30.237
Micah, chapter six, verse seven to eight, it says, should we sacrifice our firstborn children to pay for our sins?

13:30.798 --> 13:31.879
No, O people.

13:32.200 --> 13:33.762
The Lord has told you what is good.

13:34.363 --> 13:41.135
And this is what he requires of you to do what is right, to love mercy and to walk humbly with your God.

13:43.058 --> 13:45.682
Now I heard this account of Abraham as a child.

13:46.242 --> 13:49.106
And so I've known the outcome of this story for a long time.

13:49.646 --> 13:54.252
And when you know the ending of something, it just makes the beginning a little bit easier to stomach.

13:55.393 --> 13:59.559
But I don't want to jump there because Abraham did not have that luxury.

14:00.460 --> 14:02.703
And for him, this test was real.

14:03.383 --> 14:05.927
And unlike us, he did not know that it was a test.

14:06.788 --> 14:09.891
Verse three tells us that Abraham got up early the next morning.

14:11.193 --> 14:11.954
It's possible.

14:12.290 --> 14:18.836
That because of the incredible obedience of Abraham, he was up early and without delay, he was just willing to do whatever God asked.

14:20.918 --> 14:33.951
Now my education is in counseling and I usually try to anticipate the situation and anticipate how a situation has made someone feel so that I can emphasize with them.

14:35.012 --> 14:41.618
And I struggle to believe that Abraham jumped out of bed, just feeling ready for what he was about to do.

14:42.370 --> 14:45.014
See that type of thinking denies Abraham's humanness.

14:45.895 --> 14:49.540
I believe that's more likely that Abraham, he couldn't sleep.

14:50.321 --> 14:51.843
So he was just up already.

14:52.884 --> 15:00.375
And as each moment passed, he was tormented with the confusion and the pain of thinking about what God had asked of him.

15:01.055 --> 15:11.730
And similar to Genesis chapter 12, when God made a covenant with Abraham, once again, in Genesis 22, Abraham is told to leave his family, go to the land that God would show him.

15:12.962 --> 15:26.248
With what is being asked of him to do, I'm certain he had to just get away from his family because he knew that with what was happening and if he had told them what was happening, they would have tried to stop him.

15:27.951 --> 15:29.554
There is no way he told Sarah.

15:30.146 --> 15:34.132
His wife had lived most of her life in disgrace because she was barren.

15:34.493 --> 15:38.078
And then at 90 years old, finally, the Lord did what he had promised.

15:38.318 --> 15:39.260
She was given a son.

15:39.520 --> 15:41.704
She was redeemed because of this son.

15:41.984 --> 15:46.010
And if Abraham had told her, God has asked us to sacrifice our son.

15:46.411 --> 15:50.577
She would have hidden Isaac or at the very least, she would have pleaded with Abraham.

15:50.858 --> 15:52.159
Don't go, don't do this.

15:52.700 --> 15:56.967
So he got up early so that he didn't have to face Sarah Abraham.

15:57.007 --> 15:59.090
He would have been in anguish.

15:59.874 --> 16:08.005
Thoughts just racing in his head says he saddled his donkey, he took two servants and his son, and then he chopped wood before he was leaving.

16:09.728 --> 16:11.851
I'm gonna guess maybe he's not fully all there.

16:12.632 --> 16:16.176
Because why not chop wood before you wake your son?

16:17.418 --> 16:22.786
Abraham's wealthy and he's old, so why didn't he ask his servants to chop the wood?

16:23.787 --> 16:26.691
Or why chop the wood at all?

16:27.051 --> 16:28.914
Was there no wood where he was going?

16:30.114 --> 16:31.155
He wasn't thinking clearly.

16:32.797 --> 16:33.438
Who would be?

16:33.458 --> 16:37.984
The text says it's a three-day journey to the place that God led them to.

16:39.565 --> 16:48.516
We don't know how old Isaac was, but we know that the text tells us he was capable of walking, likely upwards of almost 100 kilometers.

16:49.718 --> 16:50.899
He certainly was not a toddler.

16:51.520 --> 16:52.641
He was not a preschooler.

16:53.623 --> 16:56.466
It also says that he carried the wood for a while.

16:57.186 --> 17:04.754
Now, my own son is now 13, and there are times when we're walking away from the baseball field after a double header, and he asks for help.

17:05.114 --> 17:06.616
Can you help carry some of my equipment?

17:07.136 --> 17:10.620
So, I assume Isaac is older than 13.

17:12.722 --> 17:15.185
Nothing is recorded about the conversation as they traveled.

17:16.266 --> 17:20.550
It's a long walk to do in silence.

17:20.570 --> 17:23.954
I've sat beside someone as they were on their deathbed.

17:24.994 --> 17:30.140
And the thing that brought comfort was talking about how the fact that their suffering was going to end.

17:31.642 --> 17:36.067
But how could Abraham just look at his healthy young son?

17:37.428 --> 17:38.910
How could he have any words to say?

17:40.291 --> 17:46.999
The only thing he would have been thinking about is what's gonna happen when they arrive at the place where God had told him to go?

17:48.641 --> 17:53.266
We thank God for our friends and our family members who can help us carry our burdens

17:53.570 --> 17:56.794
But there are some trials in life that we must face alone.

17:57.835 --> 18:07.827
Abraham, he was carrying the weight of this unreasonable task all on his own, alone with his thoughts about God and what he was asking of him.

18:10.089 --> 18:10.710
After C.S.

18:10.730 --> 18:20.161
Lewis's wife died from cancer, he wrote about his grief and how it forced him to assess his understanding of God and his relationship with him.

18:20.441 --> 18:21.202
He writes this,

18:22.626 --> 18:27.596
Bridge players tell me that there must be some money on the game or else people won't take it seriously.

18:28.177 --> 18:29.219
Apparently it's like that.

18:29.600 --> 18:41.202
Your bid for God or no God, for a good God or the cosmic sadist, for eternal life or a non-entity, will not be serious if nothing much is staked on it.

18:41.698 --> 18:54.636
and you will never discover how serious it was until the stakes are raised horribly high, until you find that you're playing not for counters or for six penses, but for every penny you have in the world.

18:55.417 --> 19:03.788
Nothing less will shake a man, or at any rate, a man like me out of his merely verbal thinking and his merely notional beliefs.

19:05.310 --> 19:10.898
He has to be knocked silly before he comes to his senses, and only torture will bring out the truth.

19:13.730 --> 19:14.931
It's a life and death test.

19:16.613 --> 19:23.321
And even that did not pull Abraham away from God, but it actually further developed his trust in God.

19:24.583 --> 19:33.994
Last week, Pastor Sam mentioned, if we try to run away from a difficult situation, we'll probably meet the same problems in the new place and still have to solve them.

19:34.955 --> 19:40.882
He said, because the heart of every problem is the problem in the heart.

19:42.818 --> 19:45.982
Abraham was well aware that God would continue to test him.

19:46.703 --> 19:49.266
And I'm guessing he was tired of failing tests.

19:50.407 --> 19:52.510
Abram had been asked to sacrifice his son.

19:53.311 --> 19:57.396
And of course, wouldn't that actually prevent God from keeping his promise?

19:58.097 --> 20:00.840
To make Abraham the father of nations through Isaac?

20:02.242 --> 20:05.586
But he did not need to know how God would fulfill his promise.

20:05.826 --> 20:07.949
He simply needed to trust that he would.

20:09.070 --> 20:12.114
In moments like this, people should focus.

20:12.322 --> 20:19.771
on the promises and recount the times in life where God has previously showed up and showed off.

20:21.293 --> 20:25.538
I wish Abraham had the Psalm 77 available to him to read while he walked.

20:26.199 --> 20:27.140
The Psalmist writes this.

20:29.343 --> 20:34.870
Psalm 77, I cry out to God, when I was in deep trouble, you didn't let me sleep.

20:35.590 --> 20:37.132
I'm too distressed even to pray.

20:37.152 --> 20:38.935
And I said, this is my fate.

20:39.295 --> 20:41.778
The most high has turned his hand against me.

20:42.498 --> 20:45.761
But then, I recall all you have done.

20:46.502 --> 20:49.084
Oh Lord, I remember your wonderful deeds of long ago.

20:49.905 --> 20:51.647
They are constantly in my thoughts.

20:51.727 --> 20:53.889
I cannot stop thinking about your mighty works.

20:54.750 --> 20:57.472
Oh God, your ways are holy.

20:58.093 --> 20:59.755
Is there any God as mighty as you?

21:00.976 --> 21:02.377
You are the God of great wonders.

21:02.838 --> 21:08.423
You demonstrate your awesome power among the nations and by your strong arm, you redeemed your people.

21:10.685 --> 21:11.666
When we are tested,

21:12.930 --> 21:23.785
And when it becomes more than we can handle, because we feel forsaken by God, that is when we must remember what He is done and who He is.

21:25.607 --> 21:29.313
That is when worship is most difficult, but most important.

21:31.836 --> 21:33.238
They arrive at the land of Moriah.

21:34.460 --> 21:37.003
Mount Moriah is in Jerusalem.

21:38.365 --> 21:41.970
It occurs only once more in Scripture, but very importantly,

21:42.146 --> 21:46.332
as the site of Solomon's temple in 2 Chronicles 3 verse 1.

21:47.113 --> 21:54.983
See, God had led them to where eventually the holy of holies was going to be built, the place where God's presence would dwell.

21:56.065 --> 22:00.691
Abraham told his servants, wait with the donkey, we will go further and we will worship.

22:01.893 --> 22:06.238
This is the very first time in all of scripture that we have the word worship.

22:07.180 --> 22:07.560
Worship.

22:08.221 --> 22:11.826
It means to bow down, to lift up the greatness of God.

22:12.994 --> 22:20.883
Abraham was to worship God at around the very place where God's people would later gather together in the temple to worship for years to come.

22:22.464 --> 22:26.589
And Abraham told his servants, we will worship there and then we will come right back.

22:27.830 --> 22:30.193
Some say maybe he was being deceptive.

22:31.574 --> 22:33.016
I'm not sure what else he could have said.

22:34.317 --> 22:42.066
Hebrews 11 understood his words to be a powerful illustration of Abraham's faith that God was going to resurrect Isaac.

22:43.202 --> 22:44.424
and they walked on together.

22:46.206 --> 22:56.880
Then Genesis 22 verses six through eight says, Abraham placed the wood for the burnt offering on Isaac's shoulders while he himself carried the fire and the knife.

22:57.500 --> 23:11.058
As the two of them walked on together, Isaac turned to Abraham and said, father, yes, my son, Abraham replied, we have the fire and the wood, the boy said, but where's the sheet for the burnt offering?

23:12.642 --> 23:15.605
God will provide a sheep for the burnt offering, my son."

23:17.026 --> 23:19.909
Abraham answered, and then they both walked on together.

23:21.951 --> 23:25.635
Okay, the author just leaves so much up to our imagination, doesn't he?

23:26.415 --> 23:32.421
Isaac, he's old enough to carry the wood, but young enough to innocently ask, where's the animal?

23:33.763 --> 23:37.386
Abraham's answer, it might have been more of a prayer spoken out loud.

23:38.367 --> 23:41.330
May God provide, or

23:41.986 --> 23:43.588
It just might have been the open truth.

23:44.269 --> 23:48.635
God will provide the burnt offering, remove the comma, my son.

23:50.577 --> 23:54.462
The words, nevertheless, they were prophetic.

23:54.482 --> 23:56.725
We do not have more details about their conversation.

23:57.406 --> 23:59.008
Was Isaac naive?

23:59.408 --> 24:00.510
And was he just trusting?

24:01.251 --> 24:03.053
Or did he actually realize what was happening?

24:04.315 --> 24:05.376
They continued up the mountain.

24:05.917 --> 24:10.162
At some point, I can only assume Isaac realized

24:11.170 --> 24:17.658
Because Abraham, a senior citizen, took this teenager and placed him on the altar.

24:19.320 --> 24:21.342
Come on.

24:21.362 --> 24:24.546
Isaac submitted to offering himself as a sacrifice.

24:26.769 --> 24:31.835
Genesis 22, verses 10 to 11, and Abraham picked up the knife to kill his son as a sacrifice.

24:32.156 --> 24:35.600
And at that moment, the angel of the Lord called to him from heaven.

24:36.000 --> 24:36.481
Abraham!

24:36.521 --> 24:37.522
Abraham!

24:39.842 --> 24:42.186
Why is it that God waits until the very last moment?

24:43.868 --> 24:45.511
Maybe you've found that in your own life.

24:45.731 --> 24:46.933
You've prayed for something.

24:46.953 --> 24:50.879
You've exhausted all options and it seems completely impossible.

24:51.299 --> 24:54.544
And that's when God shows up just in the nick of time.

24:56.307 --> 24:58.069
Well, he alone gets the glory that way.

24:59.652 --> 25:00.874
We're not able to take the credit.

25:02.636 --> 25:04.098
He is the way maker.

25:05.420 --> 25:09.106
Those are the times usually when people start to take notice that

25:09.282 --> 25:12.385
is when they start to believe, he is who he says he is.

25:13.767 --> 25:20.975
Notice the urgency by calling him twice, Abraham, Abraham, yes, Abraham replied, here I am.

25:22.937 --> 25:30.965
Genesis 22 verse 12, don't lay a hand on the boy, the angel said, do not hurt him in any way, for now I know that you truly fear God.

25:31.326 --> 25:34.950
You've not withheld from me, even your son, your only son.

25:37.492 --> 25:38.994
It's revealed to Abraham,

25:39.266 --> 25:40.307
that this was a test.

25:41.528 --> 25:44.352
Abraham truly feared the Lord.

25:45.212 --> 25:48.316
Many Bible verses mention the fear of the Lord.

25:49.397 --> 25:54.983
Now it's not suggesting that we should be scared of God thinking, ah, he's gonna strike me with lightning at any moment.

25:56.425 --> 26:04.033
No, those who do not know God, they might be afraid of judgment, of eternal death.

26:05.434 --> 26:08.818
However, for the believer, the fear of the Lord is,

26:09.218 --> 26:12.242
reverent submission that leads to obedience.

26:13.504 --> 26:16.107
It's tied to loving and to serving him.

26:17.589 --> 26:24.319
Two summaries ago, I was on sabbatical and I decided to spend some time studying the topic of the fear of the Lord.

26:25.160 --> 26:35.634
I was telling my parents what I had been reading and my son, who was also there, he spoke up and he said, the fear of the Lord should not lead us away from him, but instead closer to him.

26:37.442 --> 26:39.144
Wise words out of the mouth of a child.

26:40.326 --> 26:41.527
Here's the reason why he was right.

26:42.889 --> 26:45.692
God is holy and he hates sin.

26:46.413 --> 26:50.538
So if we hate sin, we will draw closer together.

26:52.821 --> 26:53.923
But do we hate sin?

26:54.844 --> 27:02.133
In the book, when people are big and God is small, Edward Welch, he wrote, we're more concerned about looking stupid.

27:02.293 --> 27:06.258
That's the fear of people than we are about acting sinfully.

27:07.202 --> 27:08.243
That's the fear of God.

27:09.886 --> 27:13.551
As a church, we call ourselves sanctus.

27:14.472 --> 27:16.254
That is Latin for holy.

27:17.196 --> 27:18.057
God is holy.

27:18.818 --> 27:25.267
And since we are not fully yet, we will fear the Lord.

27:26.228 --> 27:32.557
Psalm 34 verse nine says, fear the Lord, you, his godly people, for those who fear him will have all they need.

27:33.758 --> 27:36.562
Abraham knew he was complete in God.

27:37.186 --> 27:49.018
There he was, leaning over his son with a knife when God provides Abraham, just exhales this huge sigh of relief as he sees a ram now caught in the thicket right near them.

27:49.858 --> 27:59.588
Verse 14, Abraham, he named the place Jehovah Jairah, which means the Lord will see to it or the Lord will provide.

28:00.549 --> 28:05.714
To this day, people still use that name as a proverb on the mountain of the Lord

28:06.242 --> 28:07.243
it will be provided.

28:09.306 --> 28:13.252
Abraham feared the Lord, and he knew the name Jehovah Jairah.

28:13.973 --> 28:17.257
That's why he was confident that God would meet every need.

28:18.079 --> 28:21.543
And the more you know someone, the easier it is to trust them.

28:22.565 --> 28:25.870
So Abraham, he sacrificed the animal instead of his son.

28:27.952 --> 28:34.802
Verse 16, this is what the Lord says, because you have obeyed me and have not withheld even your son, your only son,

28:35.010 --> 28:38.213
I swear by my own name that I will certainly bless you.

28:38.854 --> 28:46.642
I will multiply your descendants beyond number, like the stars in the sky and the sand on the sea shore, your descendants will conquer the cities of their enemies.

28:47.183 --> 28:53.650
And through your descendants, all the nations of the earth will be blessed, all because you have obeyed me."

28:56.313 --> 29:01.138
When I realized I was going to be teaching on this story, I was uncomfortable.

29:01.954 --> 29:06.942
The reality that God tests his people is something that could just push people away from wanting to know God.

29:07.823 --> 29:11.509
So maybe if we just focus on this last verse here, God blesses his people.

29:11.769 --> 29:14.453
Well, that's awesome news and God will provide.

29:14.854 --> 29:15.655
That's awesome too.

29:16.737 --> 29:19.661
But there's a reason he needs to be the one to provide.

29:20.903 --> 29:25.630
If Abraham could always do what he was supposed to do, we would not need Jesus.

29:26.672 --> 29:30.738
Abraham is an example of one who had faith and feared God

29:31.714 --> 29:35.959
He also is one who faced many tests and at many times failed.

29:36.900 --> 29:38.382
Abraham did not measure up.

29:39.183 --> 29:41.725
We do not measure up.

29:41.745 --> 29:47.512
We are blessed through Abraham because when he obeyed, through his line came Jesus.

29:48.473 --> 29:51.977
God blesses us indeed, but what did that cost him?

29:54.560 --> 29:55.841
Fast forward to the New Testament.

29:57.083 --> 29:59.826
After three years of preaching the words, repent,

29:59.970 --> 30:04.856
For the kingdom of heaven is near, Jesus knew he was about to be tested.

30:06.198 --> 30:09.583
He leapt and prayed in the garden of Gethsemane.

30:10.083 --> 30:16.412
Luke 22 verse 42 tells us, he said, Father, if you are willing, please take this cup of suffering away from me.

30:17.393 --> 30:19.896
Yet I want your will to be done, not mine.

30:22.580 --> 30:27.346
Jesus expresses the natural human desire to avoid pain and suffering.

30:28.514 --> 30:30.075
It's a test he faced alone.

30:31.337 --> 30:40.045
One commentary described it like this, like the servants of Abraham who seemed to evaporate on the day of the commanded sacrifice the disciples have scattered.

30:41.406 --> 30:43.708
And a dark hopelessness dominates Golgotha.

30:44.989 --> 30:48.092
Peter denies Christ and weeps bitter tears.

30:48.172 --> 30:49.834
Judas Iscariot hangs himself.

30:49.954 --> 30:54.799
Pilate washes his hands as the crowd in Jerusalem chance for death.

30:55.679 --> 30:56.620
The soldiers spit.

30:57.061 --> 30:58.482
They mock and beat.

30:59.842 --> 31:10.357
Jesus is prepared for death with the same painstaking care nailed to the cross with the same grim determination that Abraham used to bind Isaac for sacrifice.

31:12.019 --> 31:21.352
I suppose I need to change what I declared earlier, the most rigorous test ever given in all of history, God and his son Jesus faced.

31:22.233 --> 31:28.402
Romans 832 tells us, since he did not spare even his own son, but gave up all for us all.

31:29.346 --> 31:31.369
but gave him up for us all.

31:32.029 --> 31:33.792
Won't he also give us everything else?

31:35.654 --> 31:38.818
Abraham was tested by being asked to sacrifice his son.

31:38.918 --> 31:43.243
He was willing but did not have to because God provided a lamb.

31:44.465 --> 31:50.512
But God, he passed his own same test and he will never ask of it of us.

31:53.636 --> 31:56.620
There is a test that comes to my mind that is sort of similar.

31:57.541 --> 31:58.162
Parents,

31:58.882 --> 32:00.784
We're tested in the sense that we have children.

32:01.445 --> 32:03.647
They're in our care for at least 18 years.

32:04.828 --> 32:14.478
If we raise them, training them in the way that they should go, like it says in Proverbs 22, verse six, that means we have a responsibility as parents to teach our children what matters to God.

32:15.158 --> 32:23.847
It doesn't mean forcing them into a certain set of beliefs or rituals, rather it means demonstrating a real faith, one that puts the focus on loving God and loving others.

32:24.648 --> 32:26.930
The toughest part comes when they've grown up.

32:27.490 --> 32:35.900
and attachment has been created over the years, but once they become adults, a dependency on each other can actually be unhealthy.

32:37.182 --> 32:39.645
My oldest daughter leaves for university in a couple of weeks.

32:41.968 --> 32:53.101
Of course, I don't have the agony Abraham experienced thinking about sacrificing his child, but I'm still currently processing all the emotions of learning to let go.

32:53.122 --> 32:54.744
I'm going to miss her.

32:54.784 --> 32:56.786
That's to be expected.

32:57.250 --> 33:01.134
But there are questions that we face when we just can't hold on to someone anymore.

33:02.375 --> 33:05.478
Is my own value measured by who I am to that person?

33:06.359 --> 33:12.284
Will her absence impact my happiness in the sense that she's the source of it?

33:13.526 --> 33:19.732
The test is, does anyone meet the needs in your life that only God should meet?

33:21.353 --> 33:24.076
The test that we will all be confronted with is this.

33:24.816 --> 33:26.418
Are we gonna live by God's wisdom?

33:26.562 --> 33:27.163
or our own?

33:27.904 --> 33:32.431
Are we going to let our sin rule us or will we rule over our sin?

33:32.772 --> 33:37.359
Will we partner with God to bear his image in the world or will we live on our own?

33:38.301 --> 33:42.627
And do we trust God to be, as his name says, the provider?

33:44.030 --> 33:48.497
To summarize, will all humans face testing?

33:49.238 --> 33:49.719
Absolutely.

33:50.360 --> 33:54.386
God's testings are tailor-made for each of his child of God.

33:55.426 --> 33:57.689
And each experience is unique.

33:57.709 --> 34:02.053
Not every difficult experience in life is necessarily a personal test from God.

34:03.835 --> 34:04.656
That's worth repeating.

34:05.057 --> 34:12.485
Not every difficult experience that you are facing right now in life is a personal test from God.

34:13.666 --> 34:14.547
God's tests.

34:15.448 --> 34:18.452
They may seem unusual, but they're not always painful.

34:18.792 --> 34:24.178
Remember, Adam and Eve, they were told to eat from this tree and not from that tree.

34:24.386 --> 34:29.631
God's people in the wilderness were told, collect manna, but only six days of the week, not seven.

34:31.753 --> 34:36.018
Also, we must discern the difference between a test and a temptation.

34:36.798 --> 34:48.871
Temptations come from the desires within us, and then they're used by the enemy to bring out the worst in us, whereas a test or a trial that comes from the Lord who has a special purpose to fulfill.

34:49.451 --> 34:52.274
They're used by the Holy Spirit to bring out the best in us.

34:53.634 --> 34:56.217
I would like to lead us together in the praying of the Lord's prayer.

34:56.838 --> 35:05.909
But before I do, I want to first just pray for each of us that there would be clarity in knowing whether or not what you are facing is in fact a test.

35:06.950 --> 35:07.411
Let me pray.

35:07.972 --> 35:09.493
Lord God, you are Jehovah Jairah.

35:10.274 --> 35:13.799
Your very name speaks to your supernatural ability to provide.

35:14.600 --> 35:18.785
And as we think about things that we're facing right now, Holy Spirit, would you please bring clarity?

35:19.826 --> 35:23.090
Is it a test or is it a trial that you're allowing us to face?

35:23.714 --> 35:25.776
Or is the enemy tempting us?

35:26.477 --> 35:28.079
Is he leading us away from you?

35:29.020 --> 35:30.041
Lord, would you have mercy?

35:30.562 --> 35:36.609
Would you allow us to see the difference, help us to trust you with all our heart, our soul and our mind?

35:37.730 --> 35:38.010
Amen.

35:39.352 --> 35:45.298
And now Jesus instructed his followers to pray in a way that clearly shows confidence in knowing that the Lord will provide.

35:45.899 --> 35:51.986
And when we pray the Lord's prayer, we acknowledge we fall short and he alone meets our needs.

35:52.354 --> 35:54.116
So will you join me in praying?

35:55.317 --> 36:04.886
Our Father in heaven, hallowed be your name, your kingdom come, your will be done on earth as it is in heaven.

36:05.947 --> 36:07.328
Give us today our daily bread.

36:07.989 --> 36:11.972
Forgive us our sins as we forgive those who sin against us.

36:12.873 --> 36:22.322
Lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil for the kingdom, the power and the glory are yours.

36:22.658 --> 36:24.257
Now and forever.

36:25.754 --> 36:26.098
Amen.

